Start Jenkins: Open Jenkins in your browser.

Create Pipeline: * Click New Item -> Name it (e.g., Conference-Pipeline) -> Select Pipeline -> Click OK.

Under the Pipeline section, choose Pipeline script from SCM.

Select Git, paste your GitHub repository URL, specify your branch (usually main or master), and save.

Run Pipeline: Click Build Now in Jenkins. This will trigger the checkout, Docker build, and kubectl apply commands automatically.

Verify in Docker Desktop: * Ensure Kubernetes is enabled in your Docker Desktop settings.

Open your terminal and run kubectl get pods and kubectl get services to verify the deployment is running.

Open your web browser and go to http://localhost:30080 to view your deployed Conference Web Page.
